translation: 使用多個裝置的使用者可能會被重複計算。

description: For platforms like XBox
For the XboxOne platform

translation: 單日活躍使用者平均收入（ARPDAU）

english: Total amount of Robux earned by the experience in a day.
translation: 體驗單日賺取的 Robux 總額。

english: The daily revenue breakdown by source, e.g. game shop items, game passes, private servers, paid access, etc.
translation: 各個管道的單日收入，包括遊戲商店道具、遊戲證、私人伺服器、付費通行等。

english: Avg. revenue per user among all DAUs, measured by Robux, which equals Daily revenue / DAU.
translation: 所有 DAU 中單一使用者的平均收入，以 Robux 計算，等於單日收入除以 DAU。

english: Avg. revenue per paying user, which equals Daily revenue / Paying users.
translation: 單一付費使用者的平均收入，等於單日收入除以付費使用者。

english: % of DAUs are paying users, which equals # of paying users / DAU.
translation: DAU 中付費使用者的百分比，等於付費使用者除以 DAU。
虛擬人偶商店道具抽成

english: Breakdown filter does not apply to this chart
translation: 分段篩選不適用此圖表

english: DAU over time can help indicate whether players are consistently engaging with and returning to your game (related to retention). DAU can shift rapidly as a result of new features or content that you release and is a good way to measure the impact of updates on your players.
translation: 單日活躍使用者（DAU）趨勢可以讓您了解玩家有沒有持續地回流和進行互動（與保留率相關）。DAU 可能會因為推出新功能或新內容而改變，您可以使用 DAU 測量更新對玩家造成的影響。

english: MAU can be maintained or grown by providing regular updates that motivate your players to continue staying in the game and addressing any issues that cause players to leave (such as bugs that cause crashes or buggy states).
translation: 若要維持或增加單月活躍使用者（MAU）數量，您可以定時推出吸引玩家回流的更新，並處理令玩家離開遊戲的問題（當機、異常狀態等）。

english: Total playtime gives you a sense of how engaging your experience is over time. Break it down by age group, platform, etc to help you decide which audiences and areas you want to focus improvements on.
translation: 總時數可以讓您知道體驗在不同時段的互動性。您可以使用年齡層、平台等細分方式決定您想要針對那些受眾和領域做經營。

english: The # sessions and DAU can give you an idea if your game is engaging enough that attracts players to come back multiple times a day.
translation: 作業數和 DAU 可以幫您判斷您的遊戲的互動性有沒有足以吸引玩家單日內多次進入遊戲。

english: This metric helps you measure the effectiveness of user acquisition efforts.
translation: 這項指標可以讓您測量使用者獲取工作的成效。

english: High Day 1 retention often leads to higher overall retention for your game. If your Day 1 Retention is low or drops, that typically means that your new user experience needs to be improved. You might be losing new players early in your game because of confusing tutorials, user interfaces, lack of immediate rewards, or a too-steep immediate progression curve.
translation: 高的 1 天保留率通常會代表更高的整體保留率。如果您的 1 天保留率偏低或有下降的趨勢，您的新使用者體驗很有可能需要改善。遊戲初期玩家流失的原因包括複雜的教學或介面、獎勵不夠、進度曲線過陡等等。

english: Day 7 (D7) Retention is a good metric to track if you are hoping to make your game a daily habit - something they are motivated to play every day. If you have a low D7 retention, this may indicate an issue with engagement (new players aren't motivated to continue playing your game) or progression (players are either completing your content too quickly or taking too long to progress to the next meaningful reward).
translation: 如果您想讓玩家習慣每天都來玩您的遊戲，您可以使用 7 天（D7）保留率為指標。如果您的 D7 保留率偏低，您可以看看遊戲的互動性（新玩家沒有動力繼續玩您的遊戲）或是進度安排（玩家可能很快就完成了所有內容或花太久時間才進展到下一個階段）。

english: D30 retention helps you understand the effectiveness of converting new players to regular players.
translation: D30 存留率可以幫您了解將新玩家轉換成老玩家的成效。

english: D1 stickiness indicates the overall engagement and retention for both new and returning players who play the game every day. It can be used to understand the impact of your updates.
translation: D1 黏著率代表每天玩您的遊戲的新舊玩家的互動率和保留率。您可以用這個指標了解更新造成的影響。

english: D7 stickiness can serve as an early indicator of whether your updates lead to long term retention for your overall player base.
translation: D7 黏著率可以讓您初步了解更新對整體玩家長期保留造成的影響。

english: D30 stickiness, along with D30 retention, gives a full picture of long term retention for your game.
translation: D30 黏著率和 D30 保留率可以讓您全盤了解遊戲的長期保留情形。

english: Revenue, or total Robux earned, is the easiest metric to track for monetization. Knowing how many of your players are willing to pay money in your game and how much your players are willing to spend, among other key metrics, will allow you to understand the health of the monetization in your game and to adjust your monetization strategy more effectively.
translation: 收入（或賺取 Robux 總額）是最容易追蹤的營利指標。當您了解遊戲中有多少玩家願意花錢、願意花多少錢等資訊時，您就可以更好地掌握遊戲營利制度的好壞，並更有效地調整營利策略。

english: ARPDAU is one of the key metrics to track for monetization. You can understand the value of each player in your game and use it to estimate the change in revenue you’ll see as your DAU and MAU change over time.
translation: ARPDAU 是營利的關鍵指標之一。您可以遊戲中每一位玩家地價值，並估計 DAU 和 MAU 的變化對收入造成的影響。

english: ARPPU focuses on the players who are willing to pay for your game and is most useful when considered alongside your conversion rate. Players who buy something in your game once are often more likely to buy again. A high ARPPU typically means that your paying players are finding high, repeat value in your game and is also indicative of high player engagement.
translation: ARPPU 注重願意在遊戲中消費的玩家，和轉換率一起考慮時最能展現其用處。在遊戲中消費過一次的玩家很有可能會繼續消費。高的 ARPPU 代表付費玩家在您的遊戲中充分找到回流的價值，也代表高的玩家互動性。

english: Understanding what’s valuable in your game to players can help you figure out what to sell, how to set prices for players with varying wallet sizes, and how to design progression and economy to encourage that first purchase, and then to create longer-term paying users.
translation: 了解玩家在遊戲中最注重的環節可以幫您決定應該賣什麼東西、怎麼為不同消費能力的玩家制定價格、怎們麼設計鼓勵玩家首次消費的進度系統和經濟體系等，進而獲得更多長期付費的使用者。

english: ARPDAU and ARPPU are most useful when considered alongside your conversion rate. Conversion rate reflects how well you are able to motivate players to spend money in your game.  If you have a high conversion rate, for example, and a low ARPPU, that indicates that you are good at getting players to buy at least one item in your game, but that there is little beyond that initial purchase that inspires further spending. Understanding what is inspiring that first-time purchase and examining its value could help you determine what content you need to create to inspire more purchases.
translation: ARPDAU 和 ARPPU 在和轉換率一起考慮時最能展現其用處。轉換率代表您的遊戲能促使玩家消費的程度。比如說，如果您的遊戲有高的轉換率和低的 ARPPU，這意味著很多玩家會在您的遊戲中至少購買一樣道具，但在這之後沒有什麼會讓他們繼續消費的動機。當您了解促使第一次消費和其帶來的價值時，您就可以更好地判斷應該如何才能促使玩家繼續消費。

english: This metric helps you understand your important revenue driver so that strategically choose the area to optimize for.
translation: 這項指標可以讓您找到收入的主要來源，進而判斷應該往哪一方面著手。

english: Monetization refers to your ability to earn money from players. The KPIs help you generate actionable insights to optimize your monetization.
translation: 營利代表您從其他玩家身上賺錢的能力。您可以參考這裡的 KPI 讓您為營利進行最佳化。

english: The data is net revenue (i.e. after the fees from Roblox and the original creators), does not include refund info, and is delayed by 2 days instead of 1 day for retention and engagement metrics.
translation: 這裡的資料為淨收入（扣除 Roblox 和原創作者的費用後），不包括退款資訊，並因保留和互動指標而多延遲了 1 天（總共延遲 2 天）。

description: For desktop device
Mac OS operating system
Personal computer system
Xbox operating system

english: Total play time divided by number of sessions on each day.
translation: 總遊戲時數除以每日作業數量。

english: Average session time indicates how long a user plays each time they visit your game. You can compare it with your expectations based on your game design and genre. Break it down by age group, platform, etc. will give you an idea where to iterate your content. Use it together with D1 retention as an early indicator of your long term retention.
translation: 平均作業時間可以讓您知道使用者每一次到您的遊戲時所花的時間。您可以根據遊戲的設計和類別衡量應該達到的時間。您也可以依照年齡層、平台等類別決定遊戲更新的方向。平均作業時間和 D1 存留率可以用來初步預計長期存留率。

english: Percentage of new players in Week0 (D0-D6) who also played at any point during Week1 (D7-D13).
translation: W0（D0 到 D6）的新玩家中也在 W1（D7 到 D13）遊玩的百分比

english: W1 (Week 1) Retention is a good metric to track if you are interested in building a more casual game - something that players play on and off over time. Similarly to D7 retention, a low or declining W1 retention can indicate that there are issues with your first-time player experience or initial progression curve.
translation: 如果您的遊戲屬於休閒類型（玩家可以每隔一段時間回來玩一下），您可以將 W1（第 1 週）存留率用作參考指標。就像 D7 存留率一樣，如果 W1 存留率偏低或下降，您的首次玩家體驗或初期進度曲線可能需要改進。

english: Congratulations! You are now eligible to access the new analytics dashboards (the “Dashboards”) for your experience, which allows you to see the detailed aggregated metrics, including DAU, Average Session Time, Retention, Stickiness, etc., and break them down by age group, country, etc. Please review and accept our Terms of Service to start using the Dashboards.
translation: 恭喜您可以進入全新的體驗數據後台！您可以在後台看到 DAU、平均作業時間、保留率、黏著率等整合資料，並依年齡層、國家等項目篩選。開始使用後台之前，請先查閱並接受服務條款。

english: By clicking “Agree”, you consent to the collection and use of your users’ data by Roblox for analytics purposes. Your users’ data will only be used for calculating aggregated analytics for each experience.
translation: 您點擊「同意」即表示您同意 Roblox 為了數據用途收集並使用您的使用者的資料。使用者的資料只會用來計算每一個體驗的整合數據。

english: Additionally, by clicking “Agree” you expressly agree to maintain all the information presented in and/or derived from the Dashboards in confidence and use the information only to evaluate the performance of your Roblox experience. Further, you agree not to share, sell, publish or disseminate the information in any way.
translation: 另外，您點擊「同意」即表示您同意保密後台呈現的資訊和從後台衍生的資訊，並僅以評估 Roblox 體驗表現之用途使用該資訊。您也同意不以任何形式分享、販售、發布或流通該資訊。

english: Note: For group owned experiences, the group owner needs to turn on the “View group experience analytics” in the group role settings to allow others members to view the dashboard.
translation: 注意：若體驗為群組所擁有，群組主人必須在群組身分設定中開啟「查看群組體驗數據」才可讓其他成員查看後台。

description: Chart Tooltip in User Acquisitions
english: This daily chart shows how successful your ads are at generating play sessions. Low conversion rates can indicate opporturnity to grow your audience. Impression Conversion Rate (CVR) divides the number of associated clicks or play sessions by the count of impressions for your experience. Experience Detail CVR is the count of associated play sessions divided by experience detail page views. The End to End (E2E) CVR measures play sessions than can be attributed to an impression.
translation: 此每日圖表顯示廣告生成遊戲作業的成功率。低的轉換率表示您有很多增加受眾的機會。曝光轉換率（CVR）會將相關點擊數或遊戲作業數除以體驗的曝光數。體驗詳細資訊 CVR 是相關遊戲作業數除以體驗詳細資訊頁面查看數。端到端（E2E）CVR 計算可以歸因到曝光的遊戲作業。

translation: 您對一個問題提供了多次回答。

By submitting this questionnaire you will be making your experience unavailable in the regions listed below.

english: This experience is not eligible to see or use this feature.
translation: 此體驗沒有資格查看或使用此功能。

english: Fill out this questionnaire to ensure that your experience is compliant in all jurisdictions.
translation: 請填寫此問卷，確保您的體驗遵循所有區域的法規。

english: Note: If an update to your experience will change your answer to any questions, you are required to retake the questionnaire.
translation: 注意：如果問卷答案會因體驗更新而改變，您將必須重填問卷。

translation: 前往{linkStart}政策 API{linkEnd} 頁面了解如何讓體驗動態地符合各地法規。

english: For compliance reasons, if your experience contains the following feature(s) and does not respect Roblox’s {linkStart}policy APIs{linkEnd}, it will not be available in certain regions after you click the submit button.
translation: 因法規遵循原因，如果您的體驗含有下列功能並未遵守 Roblox 的{linkStart}政策 API{linkEnd}，您按下送出按鈕後體驗將不會在部分區域開放。

english: You will preview the Guidelines of your experience before submitting. Guidelines will only become active after you submit.
translation: 您在提交之前將會預覽體驗準則。準則只會在提交後活躍。

english: As your experience contains the following feature(s) and does not respect Roblox’s policy APIs, it is unavailable in the following region(s) for compliance reasons.
translation: 您的體驗有下列元素並違反 Roblox 政策 API，因法規遵循關係，您的體驗不會在下列地區開放。

english: You have started the questionnaire but didn’t submit. Click “Resume” to continue generating a set of Guidelines for this experience, including an age recommendation and a regional compliance assessment.
translation: 您已開始填寫問卷，但問卷尚未提交。點擊「繼續」即可繼續生成此內容的準則，其中包括年齡推薦和區域法規遵循評量。

english: Click “Start” to answer a few questions about the content in your experience. Your answers will generate a set of Guidelines for this experience, including an age recommendation and a regional compliance assessment.
translation: 點擊「開始」回答一些關於您的體驗的問題。您的答案將會用來生成此體驗的準則，其中包括年齡推薦和區域法規遵循評量。

english: Please update your response to answer a few additional questions about the content in your experience. Your answers will generate a set of Guidelines for this experience, including an age recommendation and a regional compliance assessment.
translation: 請更新回覆，並回答關於您的體驗內容的額外問題。您的答案將會用來生成此體驗的準則，其中包括年齡推薦和區域法規遵循評量。

english: The Guidelines of this experience are active as shown below. The age recommendation is now visible to users on its detail page. This experience is automatically unavailable in any non-compliant regions below.
translation: 活躍的體驗準則如下。使用者可以在詳細資訊頁面看到年齡推薦。此體驗將自動不會在下列未遵循法規的區域開放。

english: The experience will not be available in non-compliant regions
translation: 體驗將無法在未遵循法規區域營運。

english: The questionnaire validation failed. There are missing or invalid answers, please review all questions and ensure they are answered.
translation: 問卷驗證失敗，發現空白或無效答案。請再檢查所有問題，確認所有問題皆已作答。

english: Questionnaire Completed; New Submission Not Completed
translation: 已完成問卷，未完成新問卷

english:
The Guidelines of this experience are active as shown below. The age recommendation is now visible to users on its detail page. This experience is automatically unavailable in any non-compliant regions below. 
You have started a new entry for the questionnaire but didn’t submit. Click “Resume” to continue generating a set of new Guidelines for this experience.
translation: 活躍的體驗準則如下。使用者可以在詳細資訊頁面看到年齡推薦。此體驗將自動不會在下列未遵循法規的區域開放。您已開始填寫新的問卷，但問卷尚未提交。點擊「繼續」即可繼續生成此體驗的新準則。

english: You may retake the Questionnaire {boldStart}anytime{boldEnd} to accurately reflect the latest content in your experience.
translation: 您可以{boldStart}隨時{boldEnd}重新填寫問卷，讓其準確反映體驗最新的內容。

english: You {boldStart}must{boldEnd} come back and update your response if any of your answers changed (e.g. because of an experience update).
translation: 如果答案有任何變更（因為體驗更新或其他原因），您{boldStart}必須{boldEnd}回來更新您的回覆。

english: Experience Guidelines appear on the experience detail page and are used to inform search and discovery. Experiences without guidelines will show a blank label and won't get recommended to users under nine years old. Please generate Guidelines for your experience as soon as it is eligible.
translation: 體驗準則會出現在體驗詳情頁面上，並會用來為搜尋與探索提供資訊。沒有準則的體驗內容將會顯示空白標籤，且將不會被推薦給九歲以下的使用者。請在您體驗內容尚符合資格時，儘快為體驗內容產生準則。

english: {boldStart}Age Recommendation{boldEnd}: Guidelines can give users insights into the content in your experience. Parents have parental controls to customize their kids’ access.
translation: {boldStart}年齡推薦{boldEnd}：準則可以讓使用者了解體驗中的內容。家長可以使用家長監護選項調整小孩的存取權限。

english: {boldStart}Regional Compliance{boldEnd}: Guidelines can help your experience automatically become unavailable in some non-compliant regions
translation: {boldStart}區域法規遵循{boldEnd}：準則會幫助您在部分未遵循法規區域中自動停止開放體驗

english: Learn more about our {linkStart}Policy APIs{linkEnd}, which help you make your experience dynamically compliant.
translation: 前往{linkStart}政策 API{linkEnd} 頁面進一步了解如何讓體驗動態地遵循各地法規。

english: Experience Guidelines appear on the experience detail page and are used to inform search and discovery. Experiences without guidelines will show a blank label and won't get recommended to users under nine years old. Please generate Guidelines for your experience as soon as it is eligible.
translation: 體驗準則會出現在體驗詳情頁面上，並會用來為搜尋與探索提供資訊。沒有準則的體驗內容將會顯示空白標籤，且將不會被推薦給九歲以下的使用者。請在您體驗內容尚符合資格時，儘快為體驗內容產生準則。

english: {boldStart}Age Recommendation{boldEnd}: Guidelines can give users insights into the content in your experience. Parents have parental controls to customize their kids’ access.
translation: {boldStart}年齡推薦{boldEnd}：準則可以讓使用者了解體驗中的內容。家長可以使用家長監護選項調整小孩的存取權限。

english: {boldStart}Regional Compliance{boldEnd}: Guidelines can help your experience automatically become unavailable in some non-compliant regions
translation: {boldStart}區域法規遵循{boldEnd}：準則會幫助您在部分未遵循法規區域中自動停止開放體驗

english: An age recommendation provides general information about the ages of users an experience is generally suitable for.
translation: 年齡推薦能讓其他人大略知道此體驗主要針對的年齡層。

english: Descriptors highlight significant elements in an experience.
translation: 說明會點出體驗中顯著的元素。

english: Please refresh to see the updated questions
translation: 請重新整理查看更新問題

english: Non-compliant regions are where Guidelines help your experience automatically become unavailable for compliance reasons.
translation: 在未遵循法規區域中，準則會幫助您自動停止開放體驗。

english: Upon review, your latest questionnaire submission was determined to be inaccurate due to the following reasons:
translation: 我們審查問卷時，因下列原因判定問卷有誤：

english: Next Step: Please retake the questionnaire and answer accurately based on your experience content and the moderator feedback.
translation: 下一步：請重新填寫問卷，並依照體驗內容和審查員留言準確回答。

english: Click “Start” to answer a few questions about your experience. Your answers will generate a set of Guidelines for the content in your experience, which currently include an age recommendation and a regional compliance assessment.
translation: 點擊「開始」回答一些關於您的體驗的問題。您的答案將會用來生成體驗內容的準則，其中目前包括年齡推薦和區域法規遵循評量。

english: Please answer the questions accurately based on:
translation: 請依照下列事項準確回答問題：

english: the most mature/extreme content a player can possibly experience in your experience (e.g. If your experience depicts mild violence infrequently and moderate violence frequently, declare “Frequent Moderate Violence”);
translation: 玩家在體驗中能感受到的最極端 / 震撼的內容（例：如果體驗中偶爾出現輕微暴力和常常出現中等暴力，請回答「常見中等暴力」）；

english: content in any forms, including and not limited to any assets (textures, models, animations, audio, video, etc.) and/or narratives;
translation: 任何形式的內容，包括但不限於素材（紋理、模型、動畫、音訊、影片等）和 / 或描述

english: creator generated content only; user generated content is not measured. (E.g. you don’t need to account for blood in a player’s platform avatar brought into your experience.)
translation: 限定創作者生成內容，使用者生成內容不列入考量。（例：您不需要考慮到體驗中出現一名使用帶有血的虛擬人偶的玩家。）

english: Does this experience contain violence and/or violent content?
translation: 此體驗是否包括暴力和 / 或暴力内容？

english: Violence: Depictions of the act and/or the consequence of intentional, threatened and/or actual, use of physical and/or psychological force against characters and/or players.
translation: 暴力：對角色和 / 或玩家有意、威脅及 / 或實際使用物理和 / 或心理攻擊的行為和 / 或後果的展現。

english: Non-graphic character death due to accidents.
translation: 因意外發生的非血腥角色死亡。
Roblox 預設角色重置 / 死亡機制。

english: What is the level of intensity?
Mild: Implied or unrealistic depictions of violence.
translation: 輕微：暗示或不真實的暴力展現。

english: The consequence to the victim is unrealistic (e.g. blood is pixelated or discolored, bodies disappear the moment they are shot).
translation: 對受害人的後果不真實（例：血跡被馬賽克處理或被變色、被擊殺之後屍體會立刻消失）。

english: Moderate: Realistic depictions of violence that do not violate the Roblox Community Standards.
translation: 中等：不違反 Roblox 社群標準的真實暴力展現。

english: The consequence to the victim is realistic (e.g. realistic blood and/or depictions of real-life injury and death).
translation: 對受害人的後果真實（例：真實的血跡和 / 或現實生活傷害或死亡的展現）。

english: Frequent: Occurs often and/or in quick succession.
translation: 常見：常常發生和 / 或短時間頻繁地發生。

english: Unrealistic: Depictions of blood that do not look like real blood (e.g. pixelated, discolored).
translation: 不真實：看起來不像真血的展現手法（例：馬賽克、變色）。

english: Realistic: Depictions of light bloodshed that look like real blood.
translation: 真實：看起來像真血的輕微流血展現手法。

english: Are the depictions of blood infrequent and/or fleeting?
translation: 血跡的展現會不頻繁或快速帶過嗎？

english: Does this experience contain paid random items?
translation: 體驗有付費隨機道具嗎？

english: Example: The experience allows a user to receive a virtual coin in exchange for Robux.
translation: 例：使用者可以在體驗以 Robux 收取虛擬硬幣。

english: The user then goes to a different place in the experience and throws the coin into a fountain and then the user gets a random virtual item.
translation: 使用者接著可前往體驗中的不同地方，將硬幣扔進噴水池，並獲得一個隨機虛擬道具。

english: Does this experience respect the ArePaidRandomItemsRestricted policy API?
translation: 此體驗是否遵守 ArePaidRandomItemsRestricted 政策 API？
了解關於 ArePaidRandomItemsRestricted 政策 API 的資訊

english: Does this experience allow users to trade items that they paid for?
translation: 此體驗是否允許使用者交易自己付費購買的道具？

english: Does this experience respect the IsPaidItemTradingAllowed policy API?
translation: 此體驗是否遵守 IsPaidItemTradingAllowed 政策 API？
了解關於 IsPaidItemTradingAllowed 政策 API 的資訊。

english: Keep Your Account Safe With Authenticator

english: We recommend that you enable 2-Step Verification via an authenticator app to make your account more secure. This would help keep your account safe even if your password or email is stolen. If your account is compromised, Customer Support will evaluate the security measures you put in place as we try to help you recover any lost value. Learn more on our {linkStart}help page{linkEnd}.
translation: 為了確保帳號安全，我們推薦您啟用驗證器 App 雙步驟驗證。如果您的密碼或電子郵件信箱遭到竊取，您的帳號依然會受到保護。如果您的帳號遭到侵入，客服團隊在嘗試復原您的帳號內容時也會檢查您所採用的安全措施。請前往{linkStart}協助頁面{linkEnd}了解更多資訊。

english: Hi, {lineBreak}{lineBreak}We recommend that you enable 2-step verification via an authenticator app to make your account more secure. This will help keep your account safe even if your password or email is stolen. In the event that your account is ever compromised, Customer Support will evaluate the security measures you put in place as we try to help you recover any lost value. {lineBreak}{lineBreak}You can set up an authenticator app on your account by going to {securityPageLinkStart}https://www.roblox.com/my/account#!/security{linkEnd}. {lineBreak}{lineBreak}For more information, please visit our {helpPageLinkStart}help page{linkEnd}.
translation: 您好，{lineBreak}{lineBreak}為了進一步確保帳號安全，我們推薦您啟用驗證器 App 雙步驟驗證。如果您的密碼或電子郵件信箱遭到竊取，您的帳號依然會受到保護。如果您的帳號遭到侵入，客服團隊在嘗試復原您的帳號內容時也會檢查您所採用的安全措施。{lineBreak}{lineBreak}您可以前往 {securityPageLinkStart}https://www.roblox.com/my/account#!/security{linkEnd} 為帳號設置驗證器 App。{lineBreak}{lineBreak}請前往{helpPageLinkStart}協助頁面{linkEnd}了解更多資訊。

description: Localization Tables CSV management portal

english: Roblox is committed to making its websites usable by all people, including those with disabilities by meeting or exceeding the requirements of the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 2.1 Level A/AA (WCAG 2.1 A/AA).  We strive to make our sites an equal experience for everyone.{lineBreak}We continue to monitor our sites and make sure that all content provided is accessible to all visitors.  In order to help us in this process, we have engaged {linkStart}The Bureau of Internet Accessibility{linkEnd}, an accessibility consulting company, to conduct a full accessibility audit consisting of both automated and manual testing of our websites using BoIA’s A11Y® platform which provides us with specific recommendations that will assist us in ensuring that our Web presence is in conformance with the WCAG 2.1 A/AA.
translation: Roblox 致力讓所有人都可以順暢使用我們網站，也為了殘障人士符合或超過無障礙網頁規範 2.1 等級 A/AA（WCAG 2.1 A/AA）的標準。我們希望所有人都可以在 Roblox 的網站上獲得相同品質的體驗。{lineBreak}我們會持續觀察我們的網站，確保所有訪客都可以順暢使用所有內容。為了達成此目標，我們請了無障礙諮詢公司 {linkStart}The Bureau of Internet Accessibility{linkEnd} 為我們進行全面的無障礙審查，包括使用該公司的 A11Y® 平台進行自動和手動測試，並獲得符合 WCAG 2.1 A/AA 的相關指導。

english: It is important to note that efforts to the websites are ongoing as we work to implement the relevant improvements to meet WCAG 2.1 A/AA guidelines over time.
translation: 請注意，我們還在持續為了符合 WCAG 2.1 A/AA 而改良我們的網站。

english: While you are visiting our sites, you will notice that we make use of third-party sites such as Facebook, Instagram, Glassdoor, Twitch, YouTube, LinkedIn and Twitter to provide information about Roblox.  Though individuals may have challenges with access to these particular sites, Roblox does not control or remedy the way content is portrayed.
translation: 您參訪我們的網站時將會注意到我們會運用 Facebook、Instagram、Glassdoor、Twitch、LinkedIn、Twitter 等第三方網站提供更多 Roblox 的相關資訊。部分人士可能無法順暢使用所有網站，但 Roblox 無法控制或改善內容的呈現方式。

english: We use cookies to personalize and enhance your experience on our site. Visit our {privacyPolicyLink} for more information on our data collections practices. By clicking Accept, you agree to our use of cookies for the purposes listed in the settings. To see a complete list of the companies that use these cookies and other technologies and to tell us whether they can be used on your device or not, access our Cookie Consent Tool. Your will see this message only once, but you will always be able to set your preferences at any time in the Cookie Consent Tool.
translation: 我們會使用 Cookie 讓您在我們的網站上享有更加個人化、更完美的體驗。若要了解更多關於我們的資料收集作業的資訊，請前往 {privacyPolicyLink}。您按下接受即同意我們為了設定內描述的用途使用 Cookie。若要查看使用這些 Cookie 和其他技術的完整公司清單，並告訴我們能否在您的裝置上使用這些 Cookie 和技術，請使用我們的 Cookie 權限工具。此訊息只會出現一次，但您隨時可以使用 Cookie 權限工具設定偏好。

english: We want to be transparent about the data we and our partners collect and how we use it, so you can best exercise control over your personal data. For more information, please see our Privacy Policy.

english: We use this information to improve the performance and experience of our site visitors. This includes improving search results, showing more relevant content and promotional materials, better communication, and improved site performance.

english: The CPU performs all the calculations needed to run a server. CPU usage is a measurement of how many CPU cores your place is using. The most likely causes of high CPU usage are complex scripts.
translation: CPU 會執行伺服器運行所需的計算。CPU 使用量是您的地點正在使用的 CPU 核心數量。高 CPU 使用量主要由複雜的指令碼導致。

english: Memory is used to store data for rapid access in a server. Objects, settings, and player data in your world would be stored here. The most likely causes of high memory usages are complex assets and settings.
translation: 記憶體會儲存可以在伺服器中快速存取的資料。您的世界中的物件、設定及玩家資料會存到此處。高記憶體使用量主要由複雜的指令碼和設定導致。

english: Server FPS, also known as the tick rate, is the rate of Roblox engine’s core game loop. Likely causes of server FPS dropping include complex scripts, network serialization, physics, and CPU contention on the host.
translation: 伺服器 FPS（又稱更新率）是 Roblox 引擎核心遊戲迴圈的速率。更新率下降主要由複雜的指令碼、網路系列化、物理計算、主機的 CPU 競爭等因素導致。

translation: 了解 Roblox 的創作引擎──Studio

english: At Roblox, we believe you learn best by doing. Choose one of our guides to explore more of what the platform offers.
translation: Roblox認為該從做中學。請選擇一項指南，了解平台內容。

english: Our platform provides you with unparalleled opportunities to create. Get started by exploring the Creator Hub, Roblox Studio, and our vibrant Creator community.
translation: 我們的平台能提供絕佳的創作環境，開始探索創作者中心、Roblox Studio和活躍的創作者社群吧。

english: Create a New Experience in Studio
translation: 在 Studio 創造新的體驗

english: Build anything you can imagine with the all-in-one IDE for Roblox.
translation: 運用應有盡有的 Roblox 整合開發環境打造出最天馬行空的創作
在主控板管理您的創作

english: Every place is represented by a data model, a hierarchy of objects that describe everything about the place.
translation: 每個地點都會由資料模型呈現，這個物件階層會說明地點的一切內容。

english: Creating a high-quality experience demands many skills such as modeling, scripting, user interface design, and audio production.
translation: 創造優質體驗會用上許多技術，像是建模、指令碼、使用者介面設計和音訊製作。

english: Almost everything in Roblox is represented as a cloud-based asset with a unique corresponding ID.
translation: Roblox 幾乎所有東西都是雲端資產，且有相對應的唯一識別碼。

english: Workspace is a container service that holds objects that you want the Roblox engine to render in the 3D world.
translation: 工作區是一種儲存服務，能存放您希望 Roblox 引擎在 3D 世界渲染的物件。

english: Scripting lets you add custom, dynamic behavior to your experiences, providing more engaging and immersive interactions for your users.
translation: 您能使用指令碼在體驗中加入自訂、多變化的行為，為使用者提供更引人入勝且身歷其境的互動。

english: Roblox Studio is an all-in-one IDE that lets you create experiences that run on Roblox.
translation: Roblox Studio 是應有盡有的整合開發環境，您可以用來製作能在 Roblox 執行的體驗。

english: The Script Editor in Studio is the primary tool for scripting on Roblox.
translation: Studio 的指令碼編輯器是 Roblox 撰寫指令碼的主要工具。

english: The Developer Console is a tool for debugging your experience when testing in Studio or running it in production.
translation: 開發人員主機是您在 Studio 中測試體驗或是在製作過程中執行體驗時的偵錯工具。

english: The Terrain Editor lets you easily generate and alter terrain through its Create, Region, and Edit tools.
translation: 地形編輯器的建立、區域、編輯工具能方便您製作、改變地形。

english: Roblox Studio offers many debugging tools commonly found in Integrated Development Environments (IDEs).
translation: Roblox Studio 提供許多整合開發環境常見的偵錯工具。

english: A plugin is an extension that adds additional features or functionality to Studio.
translation: 外掛程式是能在 Studio 新增額外功能的擴充程式。

english: The MicroProfiler is an optimization tool available in Roblox Studio and the Roblox Client that provides detailed timing information for Task Scheduler processes.
translation: 微型分析工具是 Roblox Studio 和 Roblox Client 的最佳化工具，能提供工作排程器的詳細時間資訊。

english: Studio has many default shortcuts and key commands that make development quicker and easier.
translation: Studios 有許多預設快捷功能和重點指令，能加快並簡化開發過程。

english: The Lighting and SoundService container services let you control and customize environmental effects.
translation: 光線與聲音服務儲存服務能控制、自訂環境效果。

english: When a user joins an experience, Roblox represents them as a Player in the data model.
translation: 使用者進入體驗時，Roblox 會以玩家的形式在資料模型中呈現。

english: Every experience needs to receive user input in some way to allow users to interact and view their environment.
translation: 每個體驗都需要有辦法接收使用者輸入的內容，使用者才能與環境互動或查看環境。

english: Every Roblox user is represented by a customizable character called an avatar.
translation: 每位 Roblox 使用者都會有名為「虛擬人偶」的自訂角色。

english: Characters typically refer to any Model objects that interact with the world or other users.
translation: 角色通常指的是任何與世界或其他使用者互動的模型物件。

english: Layered clothing are cosmetic outfit accessories that naturally stretch and fit over any avatar body and existing layered items.
translation: 分層衣物是用來裝飾外觀的服裝物件，會根據虛擬人偶身體或現有的分層物品，自然延伸和包覆。

english: NPCs (non-player characters) can add a lot of depth to an experience.
translation: NPC（非玩家角色）可以為體驗增添許多深度。

english: A head part that supports facial animation is a specialized skinned head MeshPart.
translation: 支援臉部動畫的頭部是帶有皮膚的特製頭部 MeshPart。

english: An R15 humanoid character model, such as those that make up user avatar characters, is made up of 15 individual mesh objects.
translation: R15 人形角色模型，與使用者虛擬人偶角色使用的模型相同，由 15 個獨立的網格物件構成。

english: Animation is the process of applying movement and motion to your characters, objects, and environments to create an engaging and dynamic experience.
translation: 動畫能為您的角色、物件、環境套用移動與動作，創造出更具引人入勝且更具變化的體驗。

english: Character models require a specific set of components and configuration standards to ensure all avatar features work as expected.
translation: 角色模型需要特定元件和配置標準，確保所有虛擬人偶的功能如期運作。

english: Roblox's user base is distinct from other platforms in both its demographics and its expectations.
translation: Roblox 的使用者群體在人口統計資料與期望上都與其他平台有所區別。

english: Promotion on Roblox allows you to engage a global audience to drive traffic and awareness to your experiences, avatar items, and social media.
translation: Roblox 的宣傳能讓您接觸到全球的受眾，提升體驗、虛擬人偶項目、社交媒體的流量和能見度。

english: Advertising on Roblox is an opportunity to engage a global audience and drive traffic to your content.
translation: Roblox 的廣告會讓您接觸到全球的受眾，提升您內容的流量。

english: Roblox users come from a variety of cultures around the world and speak different languages.
translation: Roblox 使用者來自世界各地的各種文化，所說的語言也各有不同。

english: Cultivating an active player base is an instrumental part of developing a successful and enduring game.
translation: 培養活躍的玩家群體才能營造出成功且歷久不衰的遊戲。

english: Social features provide ways for players to play with friends and interact with other players.
translation: 玩家能藉由社交功與朋友同樂，以及與其他玩家互動。

english: EventSequencer is a powerful framework that enables you to build live, cross-server events and cutscenes on a structured sequence of actions and triggers.
translation: 活動排程器是個強大的架構，能讓您以有結構的行動與觸發次序建立即時、跨伺服器的活動和過場動畫。
在文件中找到更多教學

english: Participate in community events held by other Creators
translation: 參與其他創作者舉辦的社群活動

english: Read the latest announcements from Roblox Staff
translation: 閱讀 Roblox 工作人員的最新公告

english: Our platform provides you with unparalleled opportunities to create.
translation: 我們的平台能提供絕佳的創作機會。

english: This member is read only. Attempting to write to this member causes an error.

translation: 此成員未在物件瀏覽器出現，不應廣泛使用。

english: Roblox does not replicate this member across its server-client boundary.
translation: Roblox 不會跨越伺服器與用戶端界限而複製此成員。

english: This function returns immediately if possible, but can yield the thread that called it until it can return a value.
translation: 此函式將允許時將會立刻傳回，但在能傳回值之前可以暫停呼叫自己的執行緒。

english: This function pauses the Lua thread that called it until it returns a result. This doesn’t interrupt other scripts.
translation: 此函式在傳回結果前將會暫停呼叫自己的執行緒。此操作不會中斷其他指令碼。

english: This class is a top-level singleton. Retrieve an instance of this class with the GetService function.
translation: 此類別為頂層 Singleton。使用 GetService 函式取得此類別的個體。

english: This object’s replication behavior is dependent on the player who owns it.
translation: 此物件的複製行為取決於擁有的玩家。

translation: 此為唯讀屬性，可以在未同步的執行緒讀取。嘗試寫入將會導致錯誤。

english: You can read and write to this property safely from multiple threads.
translation: 您可以安全地從多個執行緒對此屬性讀寫。

translation: 此函式無法暫停呼叫自己的 Lua 執行緒。

translation: 無法儲存開發者產品變更，請重新嘗試。

english: Webhooks allow you to send Roblox notifications to any platform that accepts webhook integration. You can create up to {webhookCount, plural, =1 {# webhook} other {# webhooks}} at a time. Learn more about {setupLinkStart}setting up webhooks{setupLinkEnd} or how to {useWebhookLinkStart}make the most of webhooks{useWebhookLinkEnd}.

english: Webhooks notify your apps about server-specific events, so you can respond to them accordingly. When an event occurs, Roblox sends an HTTP POST request with a payload to the webhook's configured URL. Learn more about {setupLinkStart}setting up outgoing webhooks{setupLinkEnd}.
translation: Webhook 會向您的 App 通知特定伺服器事件，讓您可以分別處理。事件發生時，Roblox 會傳送含有負載的 HTTP POST 請求到 Webhook 設定的網址。了解更多關於{setupLinkStart}設定向外 Webhook{setupLinkEnd} 的資訊。

A string used to provide security and authorization. More info here: https://docs.github.com/en/developers/webhooks-and-events/webhooks/creating-webhooks#secret

english: Webhooks notify your apps about server-specific events, so you can respond to them accordingly. You can create up to 5 webhooks at a time. Learn more about {setupLinkStart}setting up webhooks{setupLinkEnd} or how to {useWebhookLinkStart}make the most of webhooks{useWebhookLinkEnd}.

description: When configuring a webhook, the user has the option to make the "secret" field enabled or disabled. This label communicates that idea.
There's a field called "secret" for configuring a webhook. This action lets the user add or exclude a secret from being included in the webhook.

Users can test that their webhooks work in the UI. Our team sends a sample response to the user's desired webhook URL. This message indicates that we sent the sample response so that the user can verify their webhook url works.
english: A sample response was sent to {url}.

description: A response is a message Roblox sends to a user's webhook url. We send a sample message to the user's webhook url whenever this action is requested by the user.

Example: "Resend in 5s"

This is a countdown until the user can perform another test on their webhooks. timeRemaining is the amount of time left formatted as a number followed by "s" (seconds). We currently don't support plural ICU syntax in CreatorDashboard, so this is the current solution.
An error that appears when Roblox fails to send a test response to a user's webhook url.

english: Hello,{lineBreak}{lineBreak}{boldStart}{code}{boldEnd} is your Roblox One-Time Code. Enter it into the login screen to log in. This code will expire in 15 minutes.{lineBreak}{lineBreak}Do {boldStart}not{boldEnd} share this code. We will {boldStart}never{boldEnd} contact you to ask for it. If you did not request this code, there is no further action you need to take. If you receive numerous codes you did not request, we strongly encourage you to link a different email to your account(s) and {linkTagWithAuthenticatorHelpLinkStart}set up 2-Step Verification by Authenticator App{linkTagEnd}.{lineBreak}{lineBreak}This login request was received from {geolocation}.{lineBreak}{lineBreak}Thank You,{lineBreak}{lineBreak}The Roblox Team
translation: 您好，{lineBreak}{lineBreak}{boldStart}{code}{boldEnd} 是您的 Roblox 一次性驗證碼。在登入畫面輸入驗證碼即可完成登入。此驗證碼將在 15 分鐘後失效。{lineBreak}{lineBreak}{boldStart}請勿{boldEnd}分享此驗證碼。我們{boldStart}不會{boldEnd}主動向您要求驗證碼。如果您未要求此驗證碼，您目前不必採取任何動作。如果您持續獲得未要求的驗證碼，我們強烈建議您連結其他電子郵件地址到您的帳號，並{linkTagWithAuthenticatorHelpLinkStart}設定驗證器 App 雙步驟驗證{linkTagEnd}。{lineBreak}{lineBreak}此登入請求來自 {geolocation}。{lineBreak}{lineBreak}謝謝您，{lineBreak}{lineBreak}Roblox 團隊

english: Hello,{lineBreak}{lineBreak}Your child has requested to create an account on Roblox, an online entertainment platform that enables kids to imagine, create, and play together in immersive, user-generated 3D worlds.{lineBreak}{lineBreak}Verification Code: {code}{lineBreak}{lineBreak}Your child has provided us with a username, date of birth, and a parent's email address to create an account. To complete the account creation process, you must consent to your child’s use of Roblox.{lineBreak}{lineBreak}You must enter the code below to complete the sign up flow and consent to your child’s use of Roblox. By entering the code, you agree to the {linkTagWithTermsLinkStart}Roblox Terms{linkTagEnd}, including arbitration, and the {linkTagWithPrivacyPolicyLinkStart}Privacy Policy{linkTagEnd}, you will supervise and be solely responsible for your child’s use of Roblox, and you consent, where appropriate to the processing of your child’s personal data in connection with the Service.{lineBreak}{lineBreak}{boldStart}Parent's Guide to Roblox{boldEnd}{lineBreak}{lineBreak}We recommend that you visit our Parent’s Guide to help yourself get acquainted with our platform and find helpful tips for creating a positive experience for your kids on Roblox.{lineBreak}{lineBreak}{boldStart}Privacy{boldEnd}{lineBreak}{lineBreak}You may remove your child's account anytime by contacting customer service at https://www.roblox.com/support. Your email will not be used for any other purpose, disclosed to third parties, or combined with any other personal information collected from your child. Please review our Privacy Policy for more information.{lineBreak}{lineBreak}Thank You,{lineBreak}{lineBreak}The Roblox Team
translation: 您好，{lineBreak}{lineBreak}您的小孩已請求在 Roblox 建立帳號。Roblox 是一個讓兒童在使用者創作的沉浸式 3D 世界裡一起想像、創作和玩樂的網路娛樂平台。{lineBreak}{lineBreak}驗證碼：{code}{lineBreak}{lineBreak}為了建立帳號，您的小孩給我們提供了使用者名稱、出生日期及家長的電子郵件地址。您必須同意小孩使用 Roblox 才可完成帳號建立流程。{lineBreak}{lineBreak}若要完成註冊流程並同意小孩使用 Roblox，您必須輸入下方代碼。您輸入代碼即表示同意 {linkTagWithTermsLinkStart}Roblox 條款{linkTagEnd}，包括仲裁條例，和{linkTagWithPrivacyPolicyLinkStart}隱私權政策{linkTagEnd}。您會監督小孩使用 Roblox，並獨自為其行為負責。您也在適當情況下同意我們為了服務相關作業處裡小孩的個人資料。{lineBreak}{lineBreak}{boldStart}Roblox 家長指南{boldEnd}{lineBreak}{lineBreak}我們建議您閱讀家長指南， 讓您可以更加了解我們的平台，以及學習如何為小孩營造正面的 Roblox 體驗。{lineBreak}{lineBreak}{boldStart}隱私{boldEnd}{lineBreak}{lineBreak}您可以隨時在 https://www.roblox.com/support 請求客服人員移除小孩的帳號。您的電子郵件地址將不會用在其他用途上、洩漏給第三方組織或與其他小孩提供的其他個人資訊合併。若要了解更多資訊，請閱讀我們的隱私權政策。{lineBreak}{lineBreak}謝謝您，{lineBreak}{lineBreak}Roblox 團隊

translation: 若要登入以下帳號，請返回並選擇其他登入方式。

english: I acknowledge that I am at least 18 years old, and that I agree to [Roblox Terms](https://www.roblox.com/info/terms) and [Privacy Policy](https://en.help.roblox.com/hc/en-us/articles/115004630823-Roblox-Privacy-and-Cookie-Policy-), including the arbitration clause and revocation policy. translation: 我確認我 18 歲以上，並同意 [Roblox 條款](https://en.help.roblox.com/hc/zh-tw/articles/115004647846-Roblox-Terms-of-Use) 和 [隱私權政策](https://en.help.roblox.com/hc/zh-tw/articles/115004630823-Roblox-Privacy-and-Cookie-Policy)，包括仲裁條款和 [撤回政策](https://en.help.roblox.com/hc/en-us/articles/115004647846#eu-uk-revocation-policy)。我同意合約立即生效，並明白我會失去退出合約的權利。我同意 Roblox 每個月向我的金融卡收取此頁面顯示的總金額。我可以隨時在 [帳務設定](https://www.roblox.com/my/account#!/billing) 取消。

I agree that Stripe Inc. will store my payment information for future Roblox purchases. I allow my card to be charged the total amount shown on this page monthly. I may cancel anytime in [Billing Settings](https://www.roblox.com/my/account#!/billing).
